titleStmt.title: Case of her Grace the Dutchess of Cleaveland, the Dukes of Grafton and Northumberland, touching an annuity of 4700 l. per annum, payable out of the post-office. Offered to the consideration of the honourable House of Commons, in relation to a clause in a bill, intituled a bill for laying several duties on low wines, &c.
